The paper focuses on building fast grammar fuzzers from a programming language implementation perspective, which suggests that it could belong to the software engineering (cs.SE) or programming languages (cs.PL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses optimization techniques from functional programming and virtual machine implementation, which could also place it in the categories of cryptography and security (cs.CR), systems and control (cs.SY), or machine learning (cs.LG).
